Instead of resetting to {}, copy the corrupt file aside and FAIL the step so a human can investigate:
```
catch (e) {
  console.error('alert-state.json corrupt: ' + e.message);
  fs.copyFileSync('alert-state.json', 'alert-state.json.corrupt.' + Date.now());
  process.exit(2);
}
```
Alternatively, on parse failure, attempt to restore from `git show HEAD:alert-state.json` before resetting to {}.

